post.message: O.K. I'm a vet that ended up in Virginia because of my stint as a sonarman in a helicopter squadron. I'm 75, having retired as an architectural designer who won a design excellence award from the Tidewater AIA. I now dabble with nature's geometry using four geometries ending up with several variations of angelic forms cut out of cardboard, plywood, mirrored acrylic. The last piece - mirrored acrylic - I drove to Massachusetts to a 5 acre garden setting only to have it blown to pieces by a rare tornado shortly after I got back to Virginia Beach. I am living of off my social security only, interested only in continuing with this investigation into whatever variations continue to come through me. I would love to figure out how to make them move, how to light them, how to keep them from being destroyed, colors, The last piece cost me $1200.00 because the acrylic cost $200 for a 4x8 sheet, (I needed two sheets) $250 to have my drawings converted into an EPS file, $250 to have it cut out with a c&c machine and another $300 for 60 6 foot acrylic rods. That drained all my savings but it was still an amazing ride. Would love to join your group if you find my work a possibility.
